<h1>The Skills</h1>

<p>A skill is the practice's judgment about one conversation, written down so the
conversation goes right every time. Not a plugin — a structured collaborator with opinions
and refusals. The skills are Claude-Code-native; the <a class="chain-link" href="/framework/">artifacts
they produce</a> are tool-agnostic, and the templates are right there.</p>

<p class="caption">Each skill is known by what it produces and where it sits in the chain.
Real-session transcript renderings arrive in v2; for now, the anatomy and the source.</p>

{%- for s in corpus.skills %}
<div class="skill">
  <h3>{{ s.name }}</h3>
  <p>{{ s.lede }}</p>
  <p class="anatomy">Claude Code skill · <a class="chain-link" href="{{ s.github }}">SKILL.md source →</a></p>
</div>
{%- endfor %}

<p class="caption" style="margin-top:1.5rem">The full catalog and the two scopes it spans —
practitioner and project — are described in the framework's
<a class="chain-link" href="https://github.com/sageframe-no-kaji/ho-system/blob/main/skills/ho-skill-overview.md">skills overview</a>.</p>
